Role: UX/UI mobile app design for iOS & Android with an experienced approach
Bio:
💬 “Siarhei and his team delivered excellent work on this website wireframe and design. Their communication was top-notch, and their design skills were excellent. I had a great experience working with them, and their help with our design was instrumental in helping us become on our messaging and branding. I will definitely plan to reach out if more design work is needed.”

💬 "Thank you so much, Siarhei and team, for your beautiful work. This is the best UI/UX team I have ever worked with. I constantly tell my team how much I love my designer. I have gotten so many compliments on how beautiful my app and website design is, and I could not recommend this team enough. I'm excited to work with them more in the future."

💬 "It is one of my best experiences for engaging freelancing services in Upwork! Siarhei is extremely professional and an expert in his area of UI/UX. He helped us revamp our web and mobile application, giving us great advice and help along the project.”

With a focus on users and key business indicators (KPIs), I am able to create designs that are both user-friendly and aligned with important business metrics.

Why should you hire me on Upwork?
✅ 500+ Successfully completed projects
✅ Excellent communication skills, ensuring your project is always on track
✅ Dedicated to creating a positive and lasting relationship with my clients
✅ Creative problem-solver, always willing to go the extra mile to exceed your expectations
✅ Constantly improving my skills and staying up-to-date with the latest design trends and techniques

Project workflow includes:
- Project discussion to gather requirements and details from the client's business, product, users, competitors, and technical aspects.
- Creation of information architecture, user flow, and CJM.
- Development of wireframes and clickable prototypes.
- Agreement on the style and nature of the future project through the selection of references and creation of several design concepts for approval.
- UX design with an attractive UI and a UIKit.
- Prototyping to test the functionality and usability of the site.
- Coordination with the client at each stage to minimize discrepancies with expectations.
- Additional stages, such as surveys and UX research, may be necessary and will be included as needed.

My design toolkit includes Figma️ (mostly ❤), Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Illustrator, Xmind and After Effects for animations.

⏳ MOBILE APP
Main Page Design (Wireframe + Mockup): 4 - 7 hours.
One Inner Page Design (Wireframes + Mockups): 2 -3 hours.

⏱️ MY WORKING HOURS:
9 am - 6 pm (GMT+3), Monday – Friday (except Holidays).

If this suits you and you are looking for the best quality and expertise in UX/UI design, just contact me and we will create an amazing product for your clients 🤙 I have experience working with a variety of industries including IT, Finance, Beauty, Education, Real Estate, Sports, Marketing, Army, Food, Travel, Law, SaaS, and startups. But my experience doesn't end there - I'm always excited to work with clients from new and diverse industries!

If you have any questions just press the invite button on my profile and text me 😉 Thanks for your time and good luck!

Name: Dmitrii B.
Role: UI/UX for E-commerce / CRO / WooCommerce & Shopify Development
Bio:
I redesign SaaS and E-commerce businesses to help them excel.

User interface and user experience (UI/UX) are essential to your online business. Whether you run an e-commerce platform, SaaS company or marketplace — my team can help you craft intuitive designs that increase conversions, revenue and customer satisfaction.

My goal is to grow your business by seamlessly designing the user experience (UX) and interface (UI) of your website, mobile app, or desktop application. 

I provide a practical goal-oriented approach where I first analyze your current situation: perform UI/UX audit, check your key KPIs, analytics, do niche analysis and competitor research. The goal of this phase is to get a deep understanding of your current situation, identify the areas for improvement and come up with a plan to increase revenue. 

Next comes designing phase - UI/UX design changes that can either be applied on your existing designs (gradual approach with step-by-step application of improved designs and A/B testing their effectiveness) or building brand new designs from the ground up. (innovative approach). In scenarios we will work with your developers and marketing team to ensure that implementation is correct and generates projected business results. 

If you think we're a good fit - let's schedule a call and talk through the details. 
Dmitrii
